okawa.co.jp/product/321805000460|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (14)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-065131-6\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 15\n | RelDate         = December 25, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321809000265|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (15)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-065389-1\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 16\n | RelDate         = March 25, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321812000187|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (16)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=February 24, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-065636-6\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 17\n | RelDate         = July 25, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321904000816|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (17)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-065907-7\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 18\n | RelDate         = December 25, 2019<ref name=\"Vol 18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321908000706|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (18)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-064270-3\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 19\n | RelDate         = March 25, 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321911000934|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (19)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-064539-1\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Manga===\nA [[manga]] adaptation with art by Hiroki Kusumoto has been published online by [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s ComicWalker since 2015. As of December 23, 2019, it has been collected in seven ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes.<ref name=\"Vol 7\"/>\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header \n| OneLanguage = yes\n| Width       = 35%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 1\n | RelDate         = September 19, 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/301402001126|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 1|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-067796-5\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 2\n | RelDate         = March 22, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321511000142|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 2|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-068150-4\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 3\n | RelDate         = November 21, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321606000333|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 3|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-068664-6\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 4\n | RelDate         = June 22, 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321702000310|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 4|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-069257-9\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 5\n | RelDate         = March 22, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321710000259|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 5|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-069696-6\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 6\n | RelDate         = January 21, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321806000446|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 6|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> \n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-065197-2\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 7\n | RelDate         = December 23, 2019<ref name=\"Vol 7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321908000240/|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! 7|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-064207-9\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Anime===\nAn [[anime]] adaptation of the series was announced by [[Media Factory]] on December 14, 2018.<ref name=\"Genre\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-13/hachinantte-sore-wa-inai-desho-fantasy-light-novels-get-anime/.140795|title=Hachinantte Sore wa Inai Desh\u014d! Fantasy Light Novels Get Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 13, 2018|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref> The anime was later confirmed to be a television series, which premiered on April 2, 2020 on [[Tokyo MX]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]], and [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-06/hachinantte-sore-wa-inai-desho-fantasy-anime-ad-reveals-2020-airing/.144230|title=Hachinantte Sore wa Inai Desh\u014d! Fantasy Anime's Ad Reveals 2020 Airing|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 6, 2019|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"April\"/> The series is co-animated by [[Shin-Ei Animation]] and [[SynergySP]], with Tatsuo Miura directing the series, Takeshi Miyamoto handling series composition and Keiji Tanabe designing the characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-07/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-tv-anime-promo-video-visual-revealed/.148737|title='The 8th son? Are you kidding me?' TV Anime's Promo Video, Visual Revealed (Updated)|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 7, 2019|accessdate=July 7, 2019}}</ref> Minako Sato is composing the series' music.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-18/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-tv-anime-1st-promo-video-previews-cast-voices/.155511|title='The 8th son? Are you kidding me?' TV Anime's 1st Promo Video Previews Cast Voices|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 18, 2020|accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref> The opening theme is {{nihongo|Space-Time of the Hesitant Person|\u6642\u7a7a\u306e\u8ff7\u3044\u4eba|\"Jik\u016b no Mayoi Hito\"}} performed by Demon Kakka and Arika Takarano, while the ending theme is {{nihongo|Moonlight Monologue|\u6708\u660e\u308a\u306eMonologue|\"Tsukiakari Monologue\"}} performed by Akino Arai x AKINO from Bless4.<ref name=\"April\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-28/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-anime-2nd-promo-video-reveals-previews-theme-songs/.156944|title='The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?' Anime's 2nd Promo Video Reveals, Previews Theme Songs|publisher=Anime News Network|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> [[Crunchyroll]] will be streaming the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-15/crunchyroll-to-stream-the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-my-next-life-as-a-villainess-that-time-i-got-reincarnated-as-a-slime-season-2-so-im-a-spider-so-what-anime/.156492|title=Crunchyroll to Stream 'The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?,' My Next Life As a Villainess, That Time I Got Reincarnated as a Slime Season 2, 'So I'm a Spider, So What?' Anime|publisher=Anime News Network|date=February 15, 2020|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hachinan-anime.com/story/|title=STORY / TV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300c\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01\u300d\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=April 3, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>{{efn|All English titles are taken from [[Crunchyroll]].}}\n!Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?\n| TranslitTitle       = Hachi-nan tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!\n| NativeTitle         = \u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|2}}\n| ShortSummary        = A Japanese salaryman falls asleep before waking up and finding himself as a five year old boy named Wendelin von Benno Baumeister, during the wedding of his oldest brother Kurt and his wife Amalie. Despite being nobles, Wendelin discovers the Baumeisters are poor and only owns small farmlands which most of it will be inherit by Kurt while the rest of his six older brothers have either married into another family, finding work as a government official or soldier, leaving him nothing to inherit. Wendelin later discovers he has the ability to use magic. While searching for firewood for his family, Wendelin meets Alfred Rainford, who detected the boy's magic, saving him from a wild boar and vows to teach him how to use magic.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = A Succession Dispute? Are You Kidding Me?\n| TranslitTitle       = Oie s\u014dd\u014d tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!\n| NativeTitle         = \u304a\u5bb6\u9a12\u52d5\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|9}}\n| ShortSummary        = Wendelin decides to keep his magic a secret after learning it moves him ahead of Kurt in the line of family inheritance, risking assassination attempts from Kurt. Alfred discovers Wendelin has an extraordinarily high magic capacity. Alfred displays several unusual symptoms, cold skin, no sense of taste and bouts of physical pain. Wendelin\u2019s strange behaviour draws Kurt\u2019s attention. Wendelin decides he wants to be an adventurer instead of a lord, making Kurt less suspicious, but Adventurers Academy is expensive, so Wendelin decides to work to pay his own tuition. To help with travelling Alfred teaches Wendelin flight magic. Wendelin\u2019s father hears a rumour of a Whispering Dead nearby, a sentient corpse doomed to become a mindless zombie. Wendelin realises he means Alfred and confronts him. Alfred admits he is dead but came back as a Whispering Dead to pass on his knowledge to an apprentice. Having done so, he teaches Wendelin holy magic to purge him and let him pass to the afterlife. Years later Wendelin leaves his family to become an adventurer. \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = A Loner? Are You Kidding Me?\n| TranslitTitle       = Bocchi tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!\n| NativeTitle         = \u30dc\u30c3\u30c1\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = Wendelin attends the Adventurers Academy and wants to make friends so they can form a party but due to his lack of communications skills and high level of magic, he causes a misunderstanding with the rest of the students who mistakenly believe they are not skilled enough to join Wendelin's party. Meanwhile, three students, Erwin, Louise and Iina, shared a bond over being in the lower class and the youngest children of their families. Wanting to gain Wendelin's recognition, the three attempt to hunt large pack of wolves but are overwhelmed by their numbers until Wendelin rescues them. Due to a misunderstanding, the three believes Wendelin sees them as a burden when in reality he wants to be friends with them. The students later attend a party hosted by Duke Braihiraider who takes an interests with Wendelin as the latter's father is a vassal of Braihiraider. When the Duke asks for a private meeting with Wendelin, he asks Erwin, Louise and Iina to join him much to their surprise. Wendelin and the others learn Braihiraider brought them to meet his court wizard, Brantack Lyngstad, Alfred's former teacher, who confirms his suspicions that Alfred passed on his knowledge to Wendelin before his passing. Realising that Wendelin is not so different to them, Erwin, Louise and Iina agree to be Wendelin's friends and join his party. As a reward for returning Alfred's possessions in his magic bag to Braihiraider, Wendelin is rewarded a thousand gold coins and inherits Alfred's estate much to everyone's surprise.\n}}\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://ncode.syosetu.com/n8802bq/|Web novel}} at [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{Official website|http://mfbooks.jp/books/series/hachinan/|Light novel official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{Official website|http://hachinan-anime.com/|Anime official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|light novel|22284}}\n\n{{Shin-Ei Animation}}\n{{SynergySP}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?}}\n[[Category:2014 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Harem_anime_and_manga]]\n[[Category:Isekai anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Japanese webcomics]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Shoten manga]]\n[[Category:Kadokawa Dwango franchises]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Light novels first published online]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Shin-Ei Animation]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]\n[[Category:Webcomics in print]]\n\n{{anime-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me? \n| image           = Hachinantte Sore wa Inai Desh\u014d! light novel volume 1 cover.jpg\n| caption         = First light novel volume cover\n| ja_kanji        = \u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01\n| ja_romaji       = Hachinan tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!\n| genre           = [[Fantasy]], [[Harem]]<ref name=\"Genre\"/><!-- Genres should be based on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = novel series\n| author          = Y.A\n| illustrator     =\n| publisher       = [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]\n| first           = June 2013\n| last            = March 2017\n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Y.A.\n| illustrator     = Fuzichoco\n| publisher       = [[Media Factory]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| imprint         = MF Books\n| demographic     = Male\n| first           = April 2014\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 19\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| illustrator     = Hiroki Kusumoto\n| publisher       = [[Kadokawa Shoten]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| magazine        = ComicWalker\n| imprint         = MF Comics\n| first           = 2015\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 7\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = Tatsuo Miura \n| producer        = \n| writer          = Takeshi Miyamoto\n| music           = Minako Seki\n| studio          = [[Shin-Ei Animation]]<br/>[[SynergySP]]\n| network         = [[Tokyo MX]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]], [[AT-X (TV network)|AT-X]]\n| first           = April 2, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = 12\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''The 8th Son? Are You Kidding Me?'''''|\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046\uff01|Hachinan tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!|lit. \"The Eighth Son? That Can't Be Right!\"}} is a Japanese fantasy [[light novel]] series written by Y.A. and illustrated by Fuzichoco. It was serialized online between June 2013 and March 2017 on the user-generated novel publishing website [[Sh\u014dsetsuka ni Nar\u014d]]. It was acquired by [[Media Factory]], who published the first light novel volume in April 2014 under their MF Books imprint. Eighteen volumes have been released as of December 2019. A [[manga]] adaptation with art by Hiroki Kusumoto has been serialized online via [[Kadokawa Shoten]]'s ComicWalker website since 2015. It has been collected in seven ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes. An [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[Shin-Ei Animation]] and [[SynergySP]] premiered on April 2, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nShingo Ichinomiya was once a single salaryman until he feel asleep and woke up in a fantasy world with magic as a young boy named Wendelin von Benno Baumeister, the eighth son of the noble Baumeister family. Due to his family being poor, Wendelin is unlikely to inherit anything from his father as most of the family's wealth and possessions will go to his eldest brother Kurt while the rest of his brothers have to find income by other means. While finding fire wood for his father at a nearby woods, Wendelin meets Alfred Rainford, a former court wizard who teaches the boy magic after learning Wendelin has great affinity for magic. Thanks to Alfred, Wendelin becomes a skilled swordsman and mage, leading him to become a famous adventurer known throughout the kingdom.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{nihongo|Wendelin|\u30f4\u30a7\u30f3\u30c7\u30ea\u30f3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Takuma Terashima]] (drama CD), Junya Enoki (anime)<ref name=\"Cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-05/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-tv-anime-casts-junya-enoki-asuka-nishi/.150762|title='The 8th son? Are you kidding me?' TV Anime Casts Junya Enoki, Asuka Nishi|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 5, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>, [[Shizuka Ishigami]] (young, anime)<ref name=\"cast3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-08/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-tv-anime-reveals-8-more-cast-members/.156257|title='The 8th son? Are you kidding me?' TV Anime Reveals 8 More Cast Members|publisher=Anime News Network|date=February 8, 2020|accessdate=February 8, 2020}}</ref>}} \n: Wendelin von Benno Baumeister is the main protagonist of the series. He was once a salaryman named Shingo Ichinomiya (\u4e00\u5bae \u614e\u543e ''Ichinomiya Shingo'') until he is reborn into magical world as the eight son of Artur von Benno Baumeister. Wendelin is at first worried about his well being since he is unlikely to inherit anything from his family as the youngest son until he meets Alfred Rainford, a former court wizard who teaches him magic and making him a skilled mage. As the series progress, he forms an adventurer party with his former classmates and friends, where he becomes famous not only for his powerful magic but also finding lost magical ruins and defeating powerful monsters. Eventually, he is rewarded for his accomplishments by the King where he is granted the rank of Earl, his own lands to rule and legally allowed to have a polygamous marriage. Wendelin later marries five of his of female companions and later his former sister-in-law.  \n\n;{{nihongo|Elize|\u30a8\u30ea\u30fc\u30bc|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Saori Hayami]] (drama CD), [[Asuka Nishi]] (anime)<ref name=\"Cast\"/>}}\n: Elize Katharina von Hohenheim, is a priestess and one of Wendelin's party members. Nicknamed the \"Saint\" by the people due to her kindness, healing powers and being the granddaughter of the Cardinal of the kingdom's church, her grandfather arranges a political marriage between Elize and Wendelin, hoping to secure an alliance with an upcoming popular noble with the church. Despite their arranged engagement, Elize genuinely falls in love with Wendelin as they both understands the burden of being in the spotlight. She later marries Wendelin as one of his wives as the head wife of the family.\n\n;{{nihongo|Erwin von Alnim|\u30a8\u30eb\u30f4\u30a3\u30f3\u30fb\u30d5\u30a9\u30f3\u30fb\u30a2\u30eb\u30cb\u30e0|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Showtaro Morikubo]] (drama CD), [[Hiro Shimono]] (anime)<ref name=\"cast3\"/>}}\n: Erwin is a knight and one of Wendelin's party members. A classmate of Wendelin during their days in the academy, Erwin wishes to find fame and fortune for himself rather rely on his noble family. After Wendelin becomes an Earl, Erwin pledges loyalty to his best friend as his first retainer and personal guard and later gets engage to one of his teammates, Haruka.\n\n;{{nihongo|Louise|\u30eb\u30a4\u30fc\u30bc|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Asami Imai]] (drama CD), Yuuna Mimura (anime)<ref name=\"cast2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-08/the-8th-son-are-you-kidding-me-tv-anime-reveals-more-cast-april-2020-premiere/.154115|title='The 8th son? Are you kidding me?' TV Anime Reveals More Cast, April 2020 Premiere|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019}}</ref>}} \n: Louise Yorande Aorelia Oufelbeik is a martial artist and one of Wendelin's party members. Skilled in channeling magic into physical combat, she became an adventurer after her family kicked her out for possessing excessive mana capacity. She felled in love with Wendelin since they were classmates but due to being a commoner, she at first believes she cannot legally marry him but be his mistress instead since he is a noble and faces competition with her best friend Iina, whose also in love with Wendelin. However, Wendelin reveals he loves them both and would rather make them both his wives instead. Thanks the party's fame and service to the kingdom, the King raises Louise to the rank of nobility, allowing her to marry Wendelin as one of his wives.\n\n;{{nihongo|Iina|\u30a4\u30fc\u30ca|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Eriko Matsui]] (drama CD), [[Mikako Komatsu]] (anime)<ref name=\"cast2\"/>}} \n: Iina Suzane Hirenbrant is a spearwoman and one of Wendelin's party members. The daughter of a family of spear practitioners, she became an adventurer after she forced to leave her family after she beaten and humiliated her older brothers in spear combat. She felled in love with Wendelin since they were classmates but due to her family being vassals, she at first believes she cannot legally marry him but be his mistress instead since he is a noble and faces competition with her best friend Louise, whose also in love with Wendelin. However, Wendelin reveals he loves them both and would rather make them both his wives instead. Thanks the party's fame and service to the kingdom, the King raises Iina to the rank of nobility, allowing her to marry Wendelin as one of his wives.\n\n;{{nihongo|In\u016b|\u30a4\u30cc\u30fc|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Y\u016b Sanada}} (drama CD)\n\n;{{nihongo|Vilma|\u30f4\u30a3\u30eb\u30de|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Mao Ichimichi|M.A.O]] (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n: Vilma Etol von Asgahan is an axe wielding hunter and one of Wendelin's party members. She was formerly a hunter serving the Asgahan family until the head of the family, General Edgar Asgahan, adopted her as his daughter as part of his plan to protect Wendelin from jealous nobles by presenting her as a possible fiance for him. Vilma was born with a rare condition called Hero's disease, which multiplied her metabolism many times over but also channels her mana into physical prowess many times more efficiently compared to other mages. Due to her condition, she became a hunter to feed her high metabolism and agrees to her adopted father's plan since Wendelin, a famous monster hunter, will allow her to eat various kinds of monster meat. She later also becomes one of Wendelin's wives.\n\n;{{nihongo|Roderich|\u30ed\u30fc\u30c7\u30ea\u30d2|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Tomohito Takatsuka (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: A former warrior who later serves Wendelin as his butler.\n\n;{{nihongo|Kurt|\u30af\u30eb\u30c8|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Tomokazu Sugita]] (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: Kurt Baumeister is Wendelin eldest brother and heir to the Baumeister family. Proud and arrogant of being the heir, he grows jealous of his youngest brother after Wendelin's fame as an adventurer grew. Wanting his brother's riches and assets, he joins a conspiracy with a group of nobles who are also wary and jealous of Wendelin and wants the boy assassinated. However, the conspiracy fails and Kurt himself is assassinated. \n\n;{{nihongo|Amalie|\u30a2\u30de\u30fc\u30ea\u30a8|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Yukana]] (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: Kurt's wife, the mother of his two sons and Wendelin's sister-in-law. After Kurt's death, she begins a relationship with Wendelin where she teaches him how to properly make love with his wives before their wedding. Later, both Amalie and Wedelin genuinely fall in love with each other and later becomes one of his wives.\n\n;{{nihongo|Alfred|\u30a2\u30eb\u30d5\u30ec\u30c3\u30c9|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Daisuke Namikawa]] (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: Alfred Rainford was a former court wizard and Wendelin's master. He was a famous mage who was believed to be killed during a failed campaign to exterminate dangerous monster in the forest but was revealed to have survive as a spirit. Sensing Wendelin's great potential in magic, he taught the boy all that he know before passing away peacefully. Rainford's assets and wealth are later inherited by Wendelin as his successor.\n\n;{{nihongo|Brantack Lyngstad|\u30d6\u30e9\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u30af\u30fb\u30ea\u30f3\u30b0\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30c8|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Yusaku Yara]] (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: Rainford's former magic magic teacher and later Wedelin and his party.\n\n;{{nihongo|Klimt Kristoff von Armstrong|\u30af\u30ea\u30e0\u30c8\u30fb\u30af\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u30d5\u30fb\u30d5\u30a9\u30f3\u30fb\u30a2\u30fc\u30e0\u30b9\u30c8\u30ed\u30f3\u30b0|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Masashi Yamane (anime)}}<ref name=\"cast3\"/>\n: A court wizard and Alfred Rainford's best friend.\n\n;Artur Baumeister\n: A poor nobleman and Wedelin's father who rules a small farmland. He has eight sons and two daughters, from his wife Johanna and mistress Leila.\n\n==Media==\n===Light novel===\n''Hachinan tte, Sore wa Nai Desh\u014d!'' is written by Y.A. and illustrated by Fuzichoco. The light novels has been published by [[Media Factory]], under their MF Books imprint. Nineteen volumes have been released as of March 25, 2020.<ref name=\"Vol 18\"/>\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| OneLanguage = yes\n| Width       = 35%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 1\n | RelDate         = April 25, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/301402001126|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (1)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n | ISBN            = 978-4-04-066719-5\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list \n | VolumeNumber    = 2\n | RelDate         = July 25, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/301405003173|title=\u516b\u7537\u3063\u3066\u3001\u305d\u308c\u306f\u306a\u3044\u3067\u3057\u3087\u3046! (2)|website=Kadokawa|publisher=Kadokawa Corporation|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</r