url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052555/http://www.hartford-hwp.com/archives/43/042.html |archive-date=2016-03-04 |url-status=live}}</ref> {{small|(part of {{flag|United Kingdom}})}}\n| November 10, 1985\n| March 9, 1995\n| Closed due to a passage of the government law that banned franchised restaurants in the territory. The McDonald's restaurant was located on a US Naval Air Station and was thus exempt from the law. When the base closed in 1995, the restaurant was required to do likewise.\n|-\n! 3\n| {{flag|Bolivia}}\n| October 24, 1997\n| September 30, 2002\n| Closed due to poor sales and high prices. McDonald's is trying to reenter the Bolivian market, but with no success so far.\n|-\n! 4\n| {{flag|Jamaica}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/Business/html/20051001T210000-0500_89555_OBS_MCDONALD_S_LEAVING_JAMAICA__.asp |title=Archived copy |access-date=2005-12-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051210180407/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/Business/html/20051001T210000-0500_89555_OBS_MCDONALD_S_LEAVING_JAMAICA__.asp |archive-date=2005-12-10}}</ref>\n| April 15, 1995\n| October 14, 2005\n| Closed due to governmental problems and declining sales.\n|-\n! 5\n| {{flag|Montenegro}}<br />{{small|(part of {{flag|Serbia and Montenegro|size=16px}} at the time)}}\n| June 1, 2004\n| 2007\n| A seasonal McDonald's restaurant was opened in [[Budva]], but it was closed due to the lack of location.\n|-\n! 6\n| {{flag|Iceland}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://visir.is/article/20091026/FRETTIR01/326438990 |title=V\u00edsir \u2013 McDonalds h\u00e6ttir \u00e1 \u00cdslandi |work=visir.is |access-date=1 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402032210/http://www.visir.is/article/20091026/FRETTIR01/326438990 |archive-date=2016-04-02 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| September 1, 1993\n| October 31, 2009\n| Closed down by Icelandic affiliate due to both prohibitive costs of importing foreign food products as required by McDonald's and the [[2008\u20132011 Icelandic financial crisis|collapse]] of the [[Icelandic kr\u00f3na|Icelandic krona]] in 2009. Its three former outlets were rebranded as its own chain of [[Metro (restaurant chain)|Metro]] restaurants, which offer similar services and menus with domestically produced ingredients.\n|-\n! 7\n| {{flag|North Macedonia}}<br />{{small|(named Republic of Macedonia at the time)}}\n| September 6, 1997\n| May 15, 2013\n| Closed due to a dispute in contract and contractual obligations with the franchise owner Sveto Janevski.\n|-\n! 8\n| {{flag|San Marino}}\n| July 6, 1999\n| July 6, 2019\n| The one and only McDonald's restaurant based in the country was located in [[Borgo Maggiore]]. It ceased operations on 6 July 2019, 20 years after its opening, due to its close proximity to restaurants in nearby Italian communities, which resulted in the decline of that restaurant's sales.\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{portal|Companies|Food}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Big Mac Index]]\n* [[Dell Theory of Conflict Prevention]]\n* [[Golden Arches Theory of Conflict Prevention]]\n* [[International availability of McDonald's products]]\n* [[List of countries with Burger King franchises]]\n* [[List of countries]]\n* [[Lists of restaurants]]\n* [[MaDonal]]\n* [[McDonaldization]]\n* [[McWorld]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050516082154/http://www.mcdonalds.com/countries.html McDonald's countries]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090904143732/http://www.mcspotlight.org/company/company_history.html Another chronology of openings]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050509082338/http://www.media.mcdonalds.com/secured/company/history/timeline/ Alternate chronology]\n\n{{McDonalds}}\n{{Lists of restaurants}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Countries With McDonald's Restaurants, List Of}}\n[[Category:McDonald's]]\n[[Category:Lists of countries|McDonald's Restaurants]]\n[[Category:Lists of 